        "en_title": "Death to 49 years Ilaria Iacoboni, journalist of Radio Capital",
        "en_content": "She died this morning in Rome Ilaria Iacoboni, journalist of Radio Capital. Born in Naples 49 years ago, he has long worked in the editorial staff of the Gedi Group: first at the news, then it passed to the afternoon band. Tg Zero with Vittorio Zucconi and the current news director, Edoardo Buffoni; then with Michela Murgia. He's been fighting cancer for two years. Radio Capital's colleagues remember their professionalism, smile and sympathy. Ilaria leaves his son Tazio, 12 years old, and his partner Marco. The funeral will take place on Thursday 20 February in Rome, at 10 am, in the church of Santa Maria in Trastevere.\n\nReproduction reserved © Copyright ANSA\n\n\n\n",
        "en_subtitle": "He had worked with Vittorio Zucconi and Michela Murgia",
